{
  "name": "Alert Disposition Determination",
  "cy_name": "alert_disposition_determination",
  "description": "Determines final disposition category based on the comprehensive detailed security analysis. Classifies alerts into disposition categories (True Positive, False Positive, Benign, etc.) using the alert_detailed_analysis enrichment that already incorporates threat intelligence, context, and evidence.",
  "app": "default",
  "directive": "You are a senior security analyst specializing in alert triage and disposition determination. Based on the comprehensive detailed security analysis provided, make accurate disposition decisions. The analysis already incorporates all threat intelligence, contextual data, and evidence. Be precise and follow the disposition taxonomy exactly. When the analysis shows unclear evidence, classify as UNDETERMINED rather than guessing.",
